# Sessions
## [PROJECT NAME]

> Log of AI work sessions. Each session gets its own entry.
> This file tracks continuity and momentum across sessions.

---

## How to Use

At the start of a session:
- Create a new entry at the top of this file
- Note the date, focus, and current phase

At the end of a session:
- Fill in outcomes, blockers, files changed, and next steps
- Ensure active-context.md and changelog.md are also updated

---

## Session Template

```markdown
### Session: [DATE] — [Brief Title]
**Mode**: [Brainstorming / Planning / Execution / Reflection]
**Phase**: [Phase name]
**Duration**: [Estimated time]
**Focus**: [What this session was about]

#### Completed
- ✅ [Task / deliverable]
- ✅ [Task / deliverable]

#### In Progress
- 🔄 [Ongoing task and its status]

#### Blockers
- [Blocker description, if any]

#### Files Changed
- `path/to/file`: [What changed]
- `path/to/file`: [What changed]

#### Decisions Made
- [Decision summary — see decisions.md for full entry]

#### Lessons Learned
- [Anything worth adding to lessons-learned.md]

#### Next Steps
- [ ] [First thing to do in the next session]
- [ ] [Second priority]
```

